When non-ASCII characters (eg. æøå ÆØÅ) are included in a body field, JIRA escapes them with numeric entities:

{noformat}
&#xE6;&#xF8;&#xE5; &#xC6;&#xD8;&#xC5;
{noformat}

This is legal, but apparently breaks the Notes email client, which does not understand numeric character entitites.

Since JIRA serves pages as UTF-8, there is no reason to escape these characters, so we shouldn't.

