We would like the ability to filter attachments directly in Jira. Many users have vcards which are attached to issues when they reply to them via the email alerts. We can tell our users to delete them before sending but often they fill forget. I'm sure a email handler could be written to do this as an extension to jira but out of the box attachment control would be nice.

{panel:bgColor=#e7f4fa}
  *NOTE:* This bug report is for *JIRA Server*. Using *JIRA Cloud*? [See the corresponding bug report|http://jira.atlassian.com/browse/JRACLOUD-10893].
  {panel}

Say I wish to record the number 0.9995 in a Number custom field. This is stored faithfully in the database. Unfortunately when editing the issue, the number field contains the value "1", evidently rounded up. Now when submitting the edit form, even if you didn't mean to, this field is 'edited' and you lose precision. In effect, JIRA cannot store more than 3 decimal points of precision. 

See the discussion at:

http://forums.atlassian.com/thread.jspa?messageID=257232075&#257232075

